cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with improving video distribution in wireless networks through distributed caching and device-to-device communication. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper specifically focuses on video content. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the proposed architecture involves distributed caching in femto-basestations. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the proposed architecture involves using mobile terminals as caching helpers through device-to-device communication. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses improving video throughput through caching and communication techniques.
